OL,3,CSurvivors of 'horrendous' medical
OL,4,Cscandals 'ignored' by government
OL,6,FShe said: "The mesh I had was actually
OL,7,Fscrewed into the coccyx. I'm not able
OL,8,Fto open my bowels properly. I have to
OL,9,Fdo daily irrigation. It's had a really
OL,10,Fbig impact on my life."
OL,12,FOnce considered a gold-standard
OL,13,Ftreatment, pelvic mesh was often used
OL,14,Fto treat incontinence and prolapse in
OL,15,Fwomen for many years, to give weak or
OL,16,Fdamaged tissue extra support.
OL,18,FHowever, in some the net-like implant
OL,19,Fcan erode and harden, cutting through
OL,20,Ftissue and damaging organs.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/13
